      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/test-conditions-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Experimental benchmark data obtained from FDA-published centrifugal pump hemolysis dataset (Hariharan et al. 2011). Test conditions span the intended COU operating envelope: flow rates 2.5–7.0 L/min, rotational speeds 2000–3500 RPM. Temperature (37°C), blood analog viscosity (0.0035 Pa·s), and hematocrit (40%) match clinical CPB conditions. Traceability to NIST-calibrated measurement equipment documented."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/output-comparison-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Predicted relative hemolysis index compared against experimental measurements at all 5 operating points. Mean relative error 8.3%, maximum 14.1% at highest flow-speed combination. All predictions within experimental uncertainty bands (±15% per FDA benchmark protocol). Acceptance criterion RH < 1 satisfied at all points. Quantitative comparison metrics documented in ValidationResult vr-01-hemolysis-benchmark."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), directly relevant to the COU decision of identifying worst-case hemolysis operating conditions. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress distribution, scalar stress exposure time) are mechanistically linked to hemolysis prediction via the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model. QoI selection reviewed and approved by clinical advisory panel."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl2",
      "rationale": "Validation activities conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is geometrically and operationally similar to the subject CPB device. Operating conditions in validation bracket the COU envelope. Blood analog fluid properties match clinical CPB conditions. Validation relevance score assessed as adequate for MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 4."
