      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/use-error-scoped",
      "rationale": "Scoped out at MRL 2 per ASME V&V 40 Table 3. Simulation setup and boundary condition specification reviewed by a second independent analyst. Standardized simulation setup checklist applied and archived. No use errors identified during internal review. Formal independent verification of use error not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/morrison/criteria/model-form-mrl2",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on literature consensus for low-Reynolds-number rotating machinery flows. Explicitly-flagged uncertainty: comparison of SST k-omega against Reynolds Stress Model (RSM) at two operating points shows 9–12% difference in predicted hemolysis index, contributing approximately 60% of total prediction variance per UQ analysis in vr-01-uq. This turbulence model form uncertainty is documented as a known gap. Accepted as residual risk at MRL 2 because: (1) both models predict RH < 1 at all operating points, preserving the binary accept/reject decision; (2) experimental validation agreement (mean error 8.3%) is within FDA benchmark tolerance; (3) MRL 2 does not require turbulence model sensitivity studies beyond a single literature-justified selection. The gap is explicitly disclosed to the regulatory reviewer."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
